      <c id="aspace_ref54" level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Series II: Mary Boger New York Marxist School Records</unittitle>
          <unitdate datechar="creation">1970s-2000s</unitdate>
        </did>
        <scopecontent id="aspace_c66c444f0e18078006c58bda7335a6ec">
          <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
          <p>The series contains early New York Marxist School records maintained by founding member Mary Boger. It includes NYMS documents; minutes, reports, curricula, catalogs, course syllabi and reading materials, programs, newsletters, public events documents, Marxist Education Collective documents, including conference materials; materials about the Grenada revolution and its overthrow, including tapes and slides; Science Task Force materials; Philadelphia Marxist School materials; topical files (political economy, Russian Revolution, etc.); files on several countries, including Cuba, El Salvador, Portugal, Puerto Rico, etc.; Women's movement materials; cultural magazines; and files on the World Trade Center Trial.</p>
        </scopecontent>
